"I voted today because of my children. We belong in Europe," said Gjose Tanevski, 62, a voter in the capital of Skopje.
Macedonia's Prime Minister, Zoran Zaev, his wife, Zorica and his son, Dushko, took part in the vote in Macedonia on a change in the name of the country that would open up to membership of NATO and the EU, in Strumica, Macedonia on 30 September 2018.
