"We are close to returning to the Pacific," he promised last August.
But analysts believe that it is unlikely that the court will take Bolivia’s party – and that there would be no major changes if it did.
The UN Assembly, which has its seat in the Netherlands, does not have the power to surrender Chilean territory and has stipulated that it cannot determine the outcome of possible discussions.
