According to FWC, widespread flowering is reported in the area around Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier – suggesting that the concentration is decreasing.
The bloom of algae spreads over a 210 km coastline from northern Pinellas County to southern Lee County.
There are smaller blooms about 16 km from the coast of Hillsborough County, but there are fewer than last week.
Blossoms have also been observed in Pasco County.
Medium concentrations have been reported in or at sea in Pinellas County during the past week, low to high concentrations in the seas off Hillsborough County, background concentration to high concentrations in Manatee County, background concentration to high concentrations in or in the seas off Sarasota County, background concentration to medium concentrations in Charlotte County, background concentration to high concentrations in or in the seas off Lee County and low concentrations in Collier County.
Breathing difficulties continue to be reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
Breathing difficulties in northwestern Florida have not been reported in the past week.
